  "local_port": 49314,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get the best employment attorney in Los Angeles?",
  "response": "Finding the best employment attorney in Los Angeles involves a few strategic steps:\n\n1. **Research and Identify Top Attorneys**: \n   - **Online Reviews**: Websites like Avvo, Martindale-Hubbell, Yelp, and Google Reviews can provide ratings and reviews.\n   - **Legal Directories**: Search for attorneys listed in directories such as Super Lawyers, Best Lawyers, or The National Trial Lawyers.\n   - **Bar Association**: Check with the California State Bar or the Los Angeles County Bar Association for referrals and credentials.\n\n2. **Consider Specialization**:\n   - Look for attorneys who specialize solely in employment law, as opposed to general practice attorneys. Specialization often indicates a deeper understanding of the nuances in employment law.\n\n3. **Review Experience and Track Record**:\n   - Consider the attorney's years of practice in employment law, the number of cases they have handled, and their success rate.\n   - Review significant case results and settlements to gauge their expertise.\n\n4. **Consultation and Case Evaluation**:\n   - Schedule consultations with a few top attorneys to discuss your case. Many offer free initial consultations.\n   - Evaluate their communication skills, how well they understand your situation, and their strategy for addressing your issue.\n\n5. **Ask for Recommendations**:\n   - Seek out recommendations from friends, family, or colleagues who have had successful outcomes with employment attorneys.\n   - Network within professional associations related to your field, as members may have insights into reputable attorneys.\n\n6. **Check Credentials**:\n   - Verify the attorney\u2019s credentials, including their education background and any certifications in employment law.\n   - Ensure they are in good standing with the California Bar Association and check for any disciplinary actions.\n\n7. **Fee Structure and Costs**:\n   - Understand the fee structure; whether it\u2019s hourly, contingency, or a flat fee. Make sure it fits your budget.\n   - Ask about additional costs like filing fees, administrative fees, and expenses for expert witnesses.\n\n8. **Personal Fit**:\n   - Ensure you feel comfortable with the attorney\u2019s style and level of personal attention. You want an attorney who is responsive and genuinely committed to your case.\n\n9. **References**:\n   - Request references from past clients to get firsthand accounts of their experiences with the attorney.\n\nHere are a few highly recommended employment attorneys and firms based on publicly available reviews up to 2023:\n\n- **Employment Lawyers Group** (L.A. office) led by Karl Gerber\n- **Setareh Law Group**; well-regarded for handling complex employment cases.\n- **Law Offices of David H. Feldman** for comprehensive employment law services.\n- **Rukin Hyland & Riggin LLP**; notable for their dedicated employment law practice.\n\nTaking these steps will help you find the best fit for your legal needs in employment law in Los Angeles.",
